-- Morocco Awards Consortium Coal Plant Construction Contract, Power-Gen Says
-- B y   A i d a   A l a m i
-- 2010-11-07T13:47:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-07/morocco-awards-consortium-coal-plant-construction-contract-power-gen-says.html
Morocco’s state power utility
l’Office National de l’Electricite has awarded a 1,300-megawatt
coal-fired power plant contract to a consortium led by
International Power, Power-Gen Worldwide reported, citing
l’Office.  The group will build the station in the Atlantic coastal
Safi city by the end of 2012 and will produce 27 percent of
Morocco’s electricity consumption when it reaches full capacity
in 2014, Power-Gen said on its website in a posting dated Nov.
5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
